even more than now.

606
01:05:15,130 --> 01:05:18,020
Which is why
tomorrow you must save yourself.

607
01:05:18,080 --> 01:05:21,120
You know the coal room?
Where the Rabbis study?

608
01:05:24,180 --> 01:05:27,170
Two o'clock tomorrow my friend
will meet you there.

609
01:05:27,230 --> 01:05:29,170
She wears bright red lipstick.

610
01:05:30,100 --> 01:05:33,190
Be strong, say your good byes.

611
01:05:54,080 --> 01:05:56,000
I will never see you again.

612
01:05:57,050 --> 01:06:00,140
I will never see any of you again,
any of you.

613
01:06:00,200 --> 01:06:02,160
Yes, you will, I promise.

614
01:06:03,090 --> 01:06:08,020
No, you can't promise.
Nobody can promise anything any more!

615
01:06:10,040 --> 01:06:12,180
Darling. Darling, darling,

616
01:06:14,120 --> 01:06:16,160
I love you with all my heart.

617
01:06:17,130 --> 01:06:21,050
My love for you is so big and
strong it will never go away.

618
01:06:22,060 --> 01:06:23,230
It will always be with you.

619
01:06:24,040 --> 01:06:29,150
Whenever you think of me, I will
be there, right over your shoulder.

620
01:06:29,210 --> 01:06:31,130
Forever and ever.

621
01:06:47,210 --> 01:06:49,170
- Your name?
- Aniela Procowna.

622
01:06:49,230 --> 01:06:51,230
- And where are you from?
- Krakow, Poland.

623
01:06:52,040 --> 01:06:54,100
But when I grow up I want
to live in Bavaria.

624
01:06:54,160 --> 01:06:56,140
My uncle says Germany
is much more beautiful...

625
01:06:56,200 --> 01:06:58,120
- Your name?
- Aniela Procowna.

626
01:06:58,180 --> 01:07:00,100
- And where are you from?
- Krakow, Poland.

627
01:07:00,160 --> 01:07:04,000
But when I grow up I want
to live in Bavaria. My uncle...

628
01:07:34,040 --> 01:07:35,110
Quick, quick in!

629
01:07:44,240 --> 01:07:48,200
Out, out. Get out of here.
Out, get out! Out. Out!

630
01:07:57,090 --> 01:07:58,100
I will not!

631
01:07:59,170 --> 01:08:00,160
Jasio?

632
01:08:17,110 --> 01:08:18,160
Mr. Laski!

633
01:08:20,200 --> 01:08:22,000
Out, out!

634
01:08:24,060 --> 01:08:25,220
You - come with me!

635
01:08:27,130 --> 01:08:28,240
And you, come! Move.

636
01:08:35,070 --> 01:08:37,090
Get away from here - but slowly.

637
01:08:37,150 --> 01:08:39,220
- I saw Jasio. He will get out.
- Thank you.

638
01:08:42,020 --> 01:08:43,050
Maria.

639
01:08:47,090 --> 01:08:48,100
Jasio?

640
01:08:55,150 --> 01:08:56,100
I know.

641
01:08:56,180 --> 01:08:58,180
Come. Come.

642
01:09:10,140 --> 01:09:11,130
Jasio!

643
01:09:12,200 --> 01:09:13,200
Jasio!

644
01:09:14,100 --> 01:09:15,090
Jasio!

645
01:09:15,150 --> 01:09:16,190
Jasio! No!

646
01:09:18,180 --> 01:09:20,000
Let me through.

647
01:09:21,110 --> 01:09:22,160
Jasio!

648
01:09:23,210 --> 01:09:24,220
Jasio!

649
01:09:25,110 --> 01:09:26,080
Jasio!

650
01:09:28,030 --> 01:09:29,090
Papa, papa.

651
01:09:29,210 --> 01:09:32,160
- I tried to get out but they...
- It's all right, it's all right.

652
01:09:32,220 --> 01:09:35,050
All that matters is that
we are together.

653
01:09:37,070 --> 01:09:39,210
Hold onto to me so
we don't get separated.

654
01:09:41,070 --> 01:09:42,180
Faster, faster.

655
01:09:55,220 --> 01:09:57,190
Hold on to me, hold on to me.
- Simon!

656
01:10:06,060 --> 01:10:08,210
There has been a mistake!
No! He's my son!

657
01:10:09,030 --> 01:10:11,020
My family is protected!

658
01:10:11,070 --> 01:10:12,120
All Jews inside!

659
01:10:12,180 --> 01:10:15,020
My family is protected!

660
01:10:15,070 --> 01:10:16,180
Everyone inside!

661
01:10:18,220 --> 01:10:19,200
Papa!

662
01:10:20,120 --> 01:10:21,090
Jasio!

663
01:11:46,160 --> 01:11:48,100
Papa! Papa!

664
01:12:07,130 --> 01:12:10,160
Jasio, I understand now why you
lived in the street.

665
01:12:10,210 --> 01:12:14,020
It was God's way to make you strong
so you can survive.

666
01:12:14,080 --> 01:12:16,020
Here, give him my sweater.

667
01:12:23,210 --> 01:12:26,220
I cannot do it. I'm afraid, Papa.
Please, I can't.

668
01:12:27,040 --> 01:12:30,190
- Yes, you can. Yes, you can.
- No. I can't. Please. I'm afraid.

669
01:12:35,170 --> 01:12:37,110
Jasio, listen to me.

670
01:12:38,040 --> 01:12:40,180
Land on your elbows,
keep your head down.

671
01:12:40,240 --> 01:12:43,170
- Come with me.
- Keep your head down and stay

672
01:12:43,220 --> 01:12:46,060
still until you see the train is gone.

673
01:12:46,120 --> 01:12:47,130
I love you, Papa.

674
01:12:47,190 --> 01:12:50,210
Then you must run as fast
as you can into the trees.

675
01:12:51,030 --> 01:12:54,020
I love you, Papa. Please! Come with me.
I don't want to please!

676
01:12:54,080 --> 01:12:57,170
Shh. Shh! Be quiet! You must be brave.

677
01:12:59,110 --> 01:13:03,070
I can't! Papa! I can't.
Please come with me. Please.

678
01:13:03,130 --> 01:13:04,160
One.

679
01:13:04,200 --> 01:13:06,200
- No! Please!
- One, two.

680
01:13:07,020 --> 01:13:07,220
Papa!

681
01:13:08,160 --> 01:13:09,110
Three!

682
01:13:12,080 --> 01:13:13,070
...my God.

683
01:14:28,230 --> 01:14:30,160
Look at that.

684
01:14:32,200 --> 01:14:33,200
Thank you.

685
01:14:34,020 --> 01:14:35,150
My darling.

686
01:15:00,200 --> 01:15:03,090
Children! Children, shh.

687
01:15:03,150 --> 01:15:06,120
Children, this is Anielka.
She will be joining us.

688
01:15:15,230 --> 01:15:18,120
Please don't leave me, please.

689
01:15:21,030 --> 01:15:26,210
This war will end and you will survive
to be a mother and tell your story.

690
01:15:27,220 --> 01:15:30,160
And one day, if we are both very clever,

691
01:15:32,120 --> 01:15:35,220
